name: Advaith Ravishankar
title: President
description: Advaith is an expert AI/ML engineer with over 3 years of experience working with Generative AI, Reinforcement Learning, NLP and Computer Vision. With this expertise, Advaith aims to create real-world solution and change the learning paradigm for predictive models to accurately mimic human domain expertise.

name: Jared Simpauco
title: VP Finance
description: Hello! I'm Jared, a fourth year majoring in Data Science with a minor in Cognitive Science. I enjoy rock climbing, solving puzzles, and playing basketball in my free time. I am excited to meet you all and have a fun year!

name: Kai Chester Ni
title: VP External
description: Kai is a fifth-year Data Science major at Muir College at UC San Diego. Kai believes in a future of tech where every digital citizen is respected as an individual, especially in terms of digital rights and privacy. As a Data Scientist, he hopes to bring emphasis to the real people and stories behind each data point, and work in organizations that strive to create positive influence.

name: Trey Scheid
title: VP Internal
description: Trey is finishing his bachelors in Data Science this year with a focus on LLMs. He has gained valuable knowledge from experiences ranging from a student startup to the operational efficiency and consumer packaged goods sales. He has built classification models, evaluated Operational Equipment Effectiveness, and consulted on sales controllables. In addition to his academic pursuits, he enjoys photography and fringe "sports".

name: Vrisan Dubey
title: Online Content Director
description: Vrisan is a fourth year data science student. He's super interested in basically anything data science ranging from NLP to computer vision to building out customer solutions. When its not data science, Vrisan likes playing and watching basketball and football. He'll be your best friend if you're a Golden State Warriors fan.

name: Zoe Ludena
title: Professional Events Co-Director
description: Zoe is a data scientist who works for the San Diego Sheriff's Department and is a tutor for the Halıcıoğlu Data Science Institute. Her domain is economics, but is comfortable with machine learning. She is passionate about conservation (of animals and the environment), teaching, and coding. She loves helping others in any way she can, as well as singing, baking, and hiking.

name: Sid Joshi
title: Professional Events Co-Director
description: Sid is a cognitive science student specializing in machine learning with a minor in math. With a variety of experiences ranging from working with transcriptomic pipelines for neuroscience research to rapid development of AI-powered solutions for industrial applications, Sid is passionate about data-driven problem-solving and practical machine learning. Aside from academics, he enjoys playing the violin, spending time with friends, and is an avid board game enthusiast.

name: Kaii Bijlani
title: Projects Director
description: Kaii is a second year data scientist focused on broadening artificial cognition and applying it to solve global issues. Currently he is working with the Data Science Alliance to optimize homelessness in San Diego County via analyzing its housing market, particularly by engineering features that reflect socioeconomic and geospatial attributes of housing in San Diego. Aside from getting caught up in current AI scandals and programming tomfoolery, Kaii also partakes in leaving his room -- he specializes in being slightly above average at pickup sports like soccer and basketball, and loves hikes.

name: Kylee Kim
title: Design Co-Director
description: Hi! I'm Kylee Kim, a second-year Cognitive Science student with a specialization in Design and Interaction, and a minor in Computation Social Science at UC San Diego. I'm looking to pursue UX/UI design and hope to design in a way that allows more accessibility to unreached audiences. - outside of academics, I like to play volleyball, go on late night food runs with friends, journal, and play guitar.

name: Jennifer Chang
title: Design Co-Director
description: Jennifer is an aspiring data scientist interested in exploring ML and generative AI. She has experience analyzing historical sales performance and performing time series analysis for a local medical non-profit. She loves designing visually compelling content to share with others. In her spare time, she enjoys paddling, drawing, and journaling!

name: James Yeh
title: Social Co-Director
description: James navigates the intersection of linguistics, mathematics, and cognitive science, drawing from each discipline to uncover innovative solutions to the challenges faced by modern speech recognition systems. But life isn't always about vocoding Peter Griffin’s voice onto everything. James also finds joy in life’s smaller pleasures: savoring a morning coffee at Copa Vida, playing late-night tennis, and unwinding with Twitch.tv binge sessions.

name: Nian-Nian Wang
title: Social Co-Director
description: Nian-Nian is a third year data science and math-computer science major student with an interest in machine learning and a broad curiosity for exploring data science across various domains. She has experience in developing web applications and machine learning, including projects in classification and generative AI. She will be starting research in applying machine learning to signal processing. Outside of her studies, she enjoys hiking, drinking boba, and has recently taken up tennis.

name: Jason Qin
title: Social Co-Director
description: Jason is a second year data science major at seventh college at UC San Diego. With experience in leadership, language education, and business operations, Jason has also developed diverse projects in data analysis, AI, and search systems using Python and Java.

name: So Hirota
title: DataHacks Co-Director
description: As an aspiring Data Scientist with industry experience, So brings a curious and open-minded approach to problems ranging from Anomaly Detection to Music Genre Classification. With honed communication and teamwork skills, he thrives in fast-paced multi-disciplinary environments, while applying my Machine Learning and Data Analysis skills. So is currently working on a neuro-evolutionary algorithm, with the end goal of making it play 2048!

name: Jennifer Hung
title: DataHacks Co-Director
description: Jennifer is a Fourth Year Data Science and Cognitive Science major, aspiring to understand human cognition via computation (whether it's neural networks, LLMs, or something completely new!!) She is currently a research assistant at an on campus lab, helping with developing data processing toolboxes and analyzing eye-tracking data. Beyond academics, she is eager to empower students of different backgrounds in enjoying computing. Some may know her better as the Creative Director of the Cheese Club at UC San Diego🧀

name: Kate Feng
title: Marketing Director
description: Kate is an aspiring data analyst with a strong interest in media marketing. She currently works as a Data Analysis Intern at Y Montessori and tutors at the Halıcıoğlu Data Science Institute. Outside of academics, she spends her time training with the Taekwondo club or editing videos for her YouTube channel.

name: Ansh Bhatnagar
title: Infrastructure Director
description: Ansh is an aspiring data scientist and machine learning engineer looking to connect his technical skills to his passions in sports, biology, and market analytics. He has experience in multiple software fields and is taking 3 minors in math, cognitive science, and supply chain. He enjoys the process of learning, and is particularly interested in cooking, plants, pets, football, & basketball.

name: Camille Sicat
title: Workshop Director
description: Camille is an aspiring consultant who wants to make a difference for her community. As an IRIS-HEP fellow, she has worked on the Rucio-SENSE DMM project on network monitoring usage. In her free time, she's an aspiring writer and artist.

name: Vaidehi Karve
title: Events Coordinator
description: Vaidehi is a second-year data science major also pursuing a minor in biology. In her free time, she loves to read mystery novels, go hiking, and play music with her friends.

name: Kendall Underwood
title: Reimbursement Chair
description: Kendall is a third-year data science student who is interested in consulting and biotechnology. She has worked on biomedical research projects analyzing data from DNA cells and hopes to continue finding her passion in data science. Outside of school, she likes to cook, hike, and hang out with friends and family.
